However, this doesn't:
{code}
object F {
	final val a: String = ""
}

class A {
	@MyAnnotation(name = F.a)
	var name = "fish"
}
{code}

results in:
{code}
error: annotation argument needs to be a constant; found: F.A
@MyAnnotation(name = F.a)
{code}

So the type-annotation :String breaks the whole thing, very strange...
